A list of constant values in the Mathf class:

* Epsilon: The smallest possible difference between two floats that can be distinguished. Approximates to 1.401298E-45.
* NegativeInfinity: Represents negative infinity.
* Infinity: Represents infinity.
* Deg2Rad: The conversion factor for converting degrees to radians. Approximates to 0.01745329.
* Rad2Deg: The conversion factor for converting radians to degrees. Approximates to 57.29578.
* PI: The mathematical constant Pi. Approximates to 3.141593.

Note that these values are all public static fields of the Mathf class and can be accessed directly without creating an instance of the class.


Examples: 

Mathf.Deg2Rad               : Convert degrees to radians: float rad = angleInDegrees * Mathf.Deg2Rad;
Mathf.Epsilon               : Use as a tolerance for float comparisons: if (Mathf.Abs(a - b) < Mathf.Epsilon) { // do something }
Mathf.Infinity              : A float representing infinity: float max = Mathf.Infinity;
Mathf.NegativeInfinity      : A float representing negative infinity: float min = Mathf.NegativeInfinity;
Mathf.PI: The value of pi   : float circumference = 2 * Mathf.PI * radius;
Mathf.Rad2Deg               : Convert radians to degrees: float deg = angleInRadians * Mathf.Rad2Deg;
Mathf.SmallestNonzeroFloat  : The smallest non-zero float value: float verySmall = Mathf.SmallestNonzeroFloat;
